<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n08080b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08080b">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08080b"> 80(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> under assumed name / of Ignotus</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>Current Topics</b> The report has reached us that the Past and Present Pupils of Dominican Convent, Eccles Street, are about to produce, for the benefit of the Society of St. Vincent de Paul, &ldquo;the Hidden Gem&rdquo;&mdash;a drama in two acts by Cardinal Wiseman. &ldquo;The Hidden Gem&rdquo; <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> deals with some incidents from the life of St. Alexius. Alexius, <mark>under the assumed name of Ignotus</mark>, returns as a ragged pilgrim to his father&apos;s house, whence he had secretly departed five years before to answer the call of Christ. <small> <a name="TL12jan24" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#TL12jan24"><cite title="source">The Leader</cite></a> (12 January 1924) 548/1</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Latin: <i>ignotus</i>, unknown.  <br>Raphael transcription: <a name="c02234h" href="c02all.htm#c02234h">VI.C.02:234(h)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
